<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="538" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1988,2015]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,152,251]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="538" pageId="1" pageNumber="537">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,447,1988,2015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537">Morphological diagnosis</emphasis>
. Wing base bright yellow in both sexes but wing completely yellow in female. Body black with a greenish or bluish shine. The hypandrium of the male genitalia is similar to that of the species of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[151,271,188,214]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Paxillaceae" genus="Melanogaster" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="2" pageNumber="538" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="hirtella">
<emphasis box="[151,271,188,214]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="538">M. hirtella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, but the surstyli (epandrium) are similar to those of the species of both the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[1170,1290,188,214]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Paxillaceae" genus="Melanogaster" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="2" pageNumber="538" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="hirtella">
<emphasis box="[1170,1290,188,214]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="538">M. hirtella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Macquart" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[1343,1436,188,214]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Paxillaceae" genus="Melanogaster" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="2" pageNumber="538" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="nuda">
<emphasis box="[1343,1436,188,214]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="538">M. nuda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
groups 
<emphasis box="[234,296,225,250]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="538">sensu</emphasis>
